{"id":"1512165160041840701","thread_id":"1511724653239074878","thread_name":"Add loadouts to the game","type":19,"author":{"id":"1455671165233266853","username":"chewybarka","global_name":"Chewbarka","discriminator":"0"},"content":"Ive been writing notes for months on these. Trying to be as detailed as possible. \nI also agree, loadouts should be its own inventory. My only issue is there has been inventory issues in the past. So I fear if they do stay in the load out and not the inventory, people will lose months of grind.","timestamp":"2026-06-04T18:44:28.824000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"pinned":false,"reactions":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"message_reference":{"type":0,"channel_id":"1511724653239074878","message_id":"1512102469247697058","guild_id":"948237510914486303"},"referenced_message":{"id":"1512102469247697058","author":"fearlessdave","content":"As I was writing my reply I saw you nailed all of the salient points. Without a stash to put off-spec items in you tend to clog your inventory with gear and that limits your ability to farm effectively as every decent piece of gear you obtain is 1 less item you can collect on future credit farming runs. If the loadout could have the gear already equipped to it, and not live in your inventory or stash that would also be acceptable. This would allow you to maintain 10 sets of gear, mods, weapons, etc."},"flags":0,"position":58}
{"id":"1512139397816914021","thread_id":"1511724653239074878","thread_name":"Add loadouts to the game","type":0,"author":{"id":"1210382357744328727","username":"confident_raccoon_92081","global_name":"Walker","discriminator":"0"},"content":"Absolutely 💯 % Necessary for the amount of characters and amount of gear. Changing on the fly, especially when trying to form a team for legendary or some other run, would cut down on the waiting time.","timestamp":"2026-06-04T17:02:06.631000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"pinned":false,"reactions":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"message_reference":null,"referenced_message":null,"flags":0,"position":56}
{"id":"1512110700603113543","thread_id":"1511724653239074878","thread_name":"Add loadouts to the game","type":0,"author":{"id":"286948291776741376","username":"imajes","global_name":"imajes","discriminator":"0"},"content":"Also, i think better and sticky filters for equipment is a must have. Obviously tiers, but also: enhanced or not, dps/magsize/reload time,  quality, power score, health/engineering/toughness, piercing/shred/blast, gear set, type, etc. both up and down.","timestamp":"2026-06-04T15:08:04.682000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"pinned":false,"reactions":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"message_reference":null,"referenced_message":null,"flags":0,"position":54}
{"id":"1512102469247697058","thread_id":"1511724653239074878","thread_name":"Add loadouts to the game","type":19,"author":{"id":"899379896256712744","username":"fearlessdave","global_name":"Fearless_Dave","discriminator":"0"},"content":"As I was writing my reply I saw you nailed all of the salient points. Without a stash to put off-spec items in you tend to clog your inventory with gear and that limits your ability to farm effectively as every decent piece of gear you obtain is 1 less item you can collect on future credit farming runs. If the loadout could have the gear already equipped to it, and not live in your inventory or stash that would also be acceptable. This would allow you to maintain 10 sets of gear, mods, weapons, etc.","timestamp":"2026-06-04T14:35:22.174000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"pinned":false,"reactions":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"message_reference":{"type":0,"channel_id":"1511724653239074878","message_id":"1511863794496831560","guild_id":"948237510914486303"},"referenced_message":{"id":"1511863794496831560","author":"chewybarka","content":"Yes, there should absolutely be a loadout system in the game.\n\nThere are currently 5 classes with 2 specializations each, giving players 10 possible class/spec combinations. Because of this, I believe the game should support at least 10 loadout slots. This would allow players to either maintain one loadout for each specialization or create multiple builds for their favorite classes.\n\nA loadout should save everything associated with a build, including:\n\nClass specialization\n\nOS\n\nEquipment\n\nWeapons\n\nWeapon and gear mods\n\nSkill chips\n\nThe goal should be true one-click swapping. When a player selects a loadout, their entire build changes instantly without requiring them to manually re-equip gear, mods, or chips.\n\nAs an added quality-of-life feature, the loadout menu could display the basic stats of each saved build. This would allow players to compare builds and see what their stats would look like before switching.\n\nWhile implementing loadouts, I would also like to see the Stash function as an actual stash rather than simply a mailbox. Players should be able to store gear, mods, and crafting materials for future builds. A storage limit of around 200 stash slots, combined with the current inventory limits (180 slots with Warden), would give players enough space to experiment with different builds without constantly managing inventory.\n\nA strong loadout and stash system would encourage build diversity, make experimentation easier, and significantly improve overall quality of life."},"flags":0,"position":52}
