{"id":"1512014160047640586","thread_id":"1511724653239074878","thread_name":"Add loadouts to the game","type":0,"author":{"id":"564148160935624744","username":"imford513","global_name":"ImFord","discriminator":"0"},"content":"Yes add loadouts please","timestamp":"2026-06-04T08:44:27.620000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"pinned":false,"reactions":[],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"message_reference":null,"referenced_message":null,"flags":0,"position":46}
{"id":"1511863794496831560","thread_id":"1511724653239074878","thread_name":"Add loadouts to the game","type":0,"author":{"id":"1455671165233266853","username":"chewybarka","global_name":"Chewbarka","discriminator":"0"},"content":"Yes, there should absolutely be a loadout system in the game.\n\nThere are currently 5 classes with 2 specializations each, giving players 10 possible class/spec combinations. Because of this, I believe the game should support at least 10 loadout slots. This would allow players to either maintain one loadout for each specialization or create multiple builds for their favorite classes.\n\nA loadout should save everything associated with a build, including:\n\nClass specialization\n\nOS\n\nEquipment\n\nWeapons\n\nWeapon and gear mods\n\nSkill chips\n\nThe goal should be true one-click swapping. When a player selects a loadout, their entire build changes instantly without requiring them to manually re-equip gear, mods, or chips.\n\nAs an added quality-of-life feature, the loadout menu could display the basic stats of each saved build. This would allow players to compare builds and see what their stats would look like before switching.\n\nWhile implementing loadouts, I would also like to see the Stash function as an actual stash rather than simply a mailbox. Players should be able to store gear, mods, and crafting materials for future builds. A storage limit of around 200 stash slots, combined with the current inventory limits (180 slots with Warden), would give players enough space to experiment with different builds without constantly managing inventory.\n\nA strong loadout and stash system would encourage build diversity, make experimentation easier, and significantly improve overall quality of life.","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:46:57.679000+00:00","edited_timestamp":null,"pinned":false,"reactions":[{"emoji":"❤️","count":6,"me":true},{"emoji":"🆙","count":1,"me":false}],"attachments":[],"embeds":[],"message_reference":null,"referenced_message":null,"flags":0,"position":45}
